<font color="#FF0000">ANNE, THANK YOU FOR SHARING</font><br>
<tt>Mon Nov 17 11:37:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
ANNE<br>
Great post, an honest look at ourselves and submission to God is the beginning of knowledge.<br>
When in Nam, I know that I was miraculously saved from death on at least nine occasions. Two of them were by divine intervention, it could not have happened any other way. But all that like the Jews great Red River crossing still did not turn me to the God of Israel.<br><br>
It took five years on the police force, having all that I wanted, lacking nothing. My divorce was pending but it didn't mean anything to me, she had been unfaithful while I was in Nam and we had tried to live together after that but it didn’t work out. <br><br>
It was when I was at peace, enjoying life that God intervened and there I found that comradeship and genuine trust as well as that warmth you speak about. Sometimes later I met my present wife and the Lord has tremendously blessed me, after my surrender to him.<br>
I seek him early every morning and that gives me a tremendous peace throughout the day, so that life with all of its problems are met with grace.<br><br>
May he direct all your path and I glad you are here.<br><br>
Your Son<br>
Cookie<br><br>
 <br><br>

